08/10/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The state prosecution in Sarajevo on Thursday (October 7th) indicted four current Bosnian Serb police officers on charges of mass murder, detention and torture of Muslims in the eastern part of BiH during the 1992-1995 conflict. 
Milan Peric, 49, Spasoje Doder, 49, Predrag Terzic, 41, and Aleksandar Cerovina, 39, are suspected of war crimes committed near the eastern town of Kalinovik. 
(Radio Free Europe, Vecernje Novosti - 07/10/10)
